What is Hydroxypropyl Methylcellulose (HPMC)?
Hydroxypropyl Methylcellulose (HPMC) is a semisynthetic, inert, viscoelastic polymer derived from cellulose that functions as a thickener, binder, film former, stabilizer, and water-retention agent across multiple industries. Owing to its excellent biocompatibility, non-toxicity, and multifunctional properties, HPMC is widely used in pharmaceutical formulations, construction chemicals, food products, coatings, and personal care applications.

Modern HPMC products offer advanced functionalities including:

·         High-performance Water Retention for cement-based construction materials

·         Controlled Drug Release Technology for pharmaceutical formulations

·         Film-forming Properties for tablet coatings and personal care products

·         Thickening & Rheology Control for food and cosmetic formulations

·         Superior Binding Performance for tablets and dry-mix mortars

·         Sustainable Plant-based Formulations supporting clean-label and eco-friendly products

By improving product consistency, workability, stability, and performance, HPMC enables manufacturers to enhance construction quality, optimize pharmaceutical formulations, develop innovative personal care products, and support sustainable manufacturing practices across multiple industries.

